Fellow NYC Locals (and anyone visiting), it’s that time again where we’re filling in volunteer shifts for @heartofdinner. Our Big Hearts are vital to our mission as these kind Humans who make up our Volunteer Community enable us to tangibly carry out our mission of supporting underserved Asian Elderly living in isolation and with food insecurity. 

This time, we’re seeking volunteers who are able to drive their own cars to help hand-deliver to the Elderly on @heartofdinner’s Independent Deliveries Routes throughout Manhattan, Brooklyn, and Queens. This point of Human contact is critical to our work to counter the loneliness as many of our Elderly recipients live alone and seeing our Volunteers during the delivery is what they look forward to brighten their days. 

If you’ve been looking for ways to proactively be a part of community and aren’t sure where to start, this is the perfect entryway to contribute your time. We have many moving pieces here at @heartofdinner and your volunteer efforts truly go a long way in driving impact. Please swipe through for more details and DM @heartofdinner. 

If you’d like to sign up for our volunteer-request newsletters like the ones you see in this post, head over to @heartofdinner’s LINK IN BIO and fill out the volunteer application to be added to our newsletter. 

Thanks so much in advance for your time and your curiosity to learn more ❤️

Can’t believe we have the privilege and honor to share that @heartofdinner has been chosen as an official charity partner of the 2023 @nycmarathon! We’re rolling out our application next week to begin the process of assembling 5 passionate and heart-driven individuals who will represent and raise funds on behalf of Heart of Dinner and run in the marathon on Nov 5th where over 50,000 runners from around the world will race through all five boroughs right here in NYC.

What an out-of-body experience looking back on the humble beginnings of Heart of Dinner in our small apartment in Chinatown with the broken oven pulling back-to-back all nighters writing love notes on lunchbox containers and, with the *ongoing critical support* of our champions, to now be able to spread our mission of tackling food insecurity and loneliness among our underserved Asian American elderly communities to the marathon’s global audience— grateful and inspired doesn’t even cut it. 

All of my love and gratitude to the extraordinary individuals who’ve supported Heart of Dinner along the way, their contributions gifted Heart of Dinner the wings to fly and enable our mission to continue nourishing the livelihood of some of the most vulnerable and at-risk. A very special thank you to @robecta_ who encouraged us to consider applying @heartofdinner as an official charity partner of the TCS NYC Marathon (a brand new channel for us in raising awareness & funding for HoD!) So grateful for her support in making this happen and support in seeing this through to the finish line (a shoutout to our dear @kevhlin for bringing us together!)

A loving shoutout to @nkpcreate, always ready to throw down at any moment— this outrageously talented human designed and illustrated the most uplifting, heartwarming, and beautiful digital assets for us to share the news of the marathon through visuals that align with Heart of Dinner’s mission. 

More marathon related updates will be shared over at @heartofdinner as we gear up for the event, so be sure to follow @heartofdinner to be on the lookout for posts & stories!

#tcsnycmarathon #heartofdinner #nycmarathon2023

As luck would have it, my Dad sent me a nostalgic photo out of the blue, just as I was making my way with @moonlynntsai to @forbes' #forbes3050 summit in Abu Dhabi honoring International Women's week. The summit has been an impactful platform for bringing visibility to @heartofdinner’s mission and the Asian American seniors we serve who live in severely under-resourced communities. The exchange of knowledge and transparent, vulnerable conversations among leaders across industries about our own challenges, successes, and bigger picture goals have been both hopeful and inspiring.

Seeing this photo for the first time, coupled with the summit's emphasis on women-identifying individuals in leadership roles, got me thinking about Little Yin and the remarkable women who have shaped me into who I am today. From my Ah Ma and sisters @lelinachang @melorayaru to my mom and aunts, their strength, wisdom, and love have been a constant source of inspiration. It’s also got me quietly and intimately reflecting on my own evolving identity as an Asian American queer woman and what it means to exist in these spaces all at once, and for so many of my siblings in the queer community who find resonance with the identity of “woman”. 

Keeping close to my heart the phenomenal women who have rooted for me, the nurturing female friendships I feel so lucky to have, and the support from the many women who have worked alongside me. Deeply grateful to those whose shoulders I stand on and to those who’ve moved mountains to pave the way for the next generation. 

To all of the women who inspire us daily: Happy International Women's Day, I’m in awe of your tenacity and courage 💌

#IWD2023 #3050abudhabi

Absolute dream to attend @vp and @glamourmag co-hosted Women’s History Month celebration (shoutout @sambarry @ru_wolle @tashpearlman and the entire Team Glamour!🤍)

The speeches advocating for women’s equity and liberation were truly moving and left me hopeful for the future we’re building toward. The special shoutout that @sambarry gave to us and @heartofdinner in the presence of the Vice President of the United States made it all the more touching. Real talk…that unexpected mention got me all emotional & was a grounding reminder of the life-changing impact of empathy and tenacity. 

Heart of Dinner has been a privilege to grow & uplift livelihoods alongside my romantic partner and co-founder @moonlynntsai. It’s been a powerful vehicle to confront harmful stereotypes about Asian Americans, bring attention to the often-overlooked Asian American senior population, and redistribute access to foundational human necessities to beneficiaries who have been sidelined into significantly under-resourced communities.

Grateful is an understatement to even try and begin to describe how I feel for this opportunity as a social entrepreneur to reimagine a framework that bridges intergenerational and multicultural gaps, and challenge the perception of LGBTQIA+ communities (even within my own Asian American community) by simply existing and being intentional in speaking to our identities when raising awareness about @heartofdinner and its founding story— all deeply rooted in love. Witnessing the best of humanity day in and day out among Heart of Dinner’s community of volunteers and champions has been an incredibly rewarding experience.

Standing among so many formidable women, I was reminded of the collective progress we’ve made in expanding representation, challenging stereotypes, and dignifying the nuances of our voices while building the alternate reality we want to see. 

Thank you to @vp Kamala Harris and @glamourmag for this joyous gathering. ❤️

👗 Thank you so much Team @31philliplim for dressing us in the best!! 

#WomenEmpoweringWomen #RepresentationMatters #WomensHistoryMonth #InclusiveLeadership

This moment will forever leave me on Cloud 9. Vice President Kamala Harris’ leadership and dedication as a champion of women are truly remarkable, and I’m thankful for the raised bar that she sets for people worldwide. To stand here in the same room…grateful and honored doesn’t even cut it.

I can't stop thinking of the countless women and their contributions that led me to this room. From @chanel_miller who single-handedly brought my and Moonlynn’s names to the table during her time on the Advisory Board of @glamourmag Women of the Year; to the other advisory board members who passionately agreed with her nomination (I will always cherish the moment when some of my absolute fav humans, @iammarleydias @drjanicejohnson, shared how excited they were to learn about us and root for us!); to the decision of the inimitable EIC @sambarry and Team Glamour and their ongoing uplifting since, all helped pave the way for this exact moment.

I'm in awe of how interconnected our world is where every effort can make a difference and have a far-reaching and lasting impact. Experiencing this butterfly effect makes it even more humbling for me to participate in the Glamour Women of the Year advisory board. I'm more invigorated and committed than ever to keeping our eyes on the prize of opening more doors and gateways for women.

From the very start of this journey— observing my Grandma's kindness and strength, my Mom’s unstoppable drive and entrepreneurial spirit, my sisters @lelinachang @melorayaru inspiring values and unwavering support, my beautiful partner @moonlynntsai’s perseverance and ever-flowing love, and all those who have been present in my life— every step along the way has been marked by empowering and uplifting support from women. 

Thank you, @vp Harris and @glamourmag, for being such unwavering advocates and spurring us to keep pushing forward. Thank you, Glamour, for co-hosting this memory of a lifetime. My heartfelt love and gratitude to @therealphilliplim and Team @31philliplim for dressing me in the most exquisite armor. 

#womenshistorymonth #womensupportingwomen

YESSSSS💥💥💥 Head over to @disneyplus ASAP and start binging @ambornchinese!! This show is an American feat in its effortless storytelling, weaving in and out of laugh-out-loud, endearing, heart-tugging, and tear-jerking moments that feel deeply personal in universal ways. First learned about @geneluenyang through my beloved @88cupsoftea community of storytellers and writers, adored throughout for masterfully captivating readers with his graphic novels & comics. Absolutely awe-inspiring to see his award winning graphic novel series being adapted into TV so thoughtfully🥹🙌🎉

What an honor to attend the groundbreaking world premiere of American Born Chinese at Radio City Hall. The entire room full of Asian Americans and community allies and friends, buzzing with anticipation and excitement, it was an out-of-body experience to be deeply aware that a historic moment was happening right at that very moment and to experience it with @moonlynntsai and my sisters @lelinachang @melorayaru are memories I’ll forever cherish.

Our elderly generations could never have imagined a day where people who look like us are seen and celebrated in all our dimensions, right here in one of the world's most iconic venues, rich in American history. I’ve yet to find words worthy enough to capture the feeling.

A massive congratulations to the entire crew and cast who‘ve worked tirelessly to break barriers and bring this project to life. This is a win for all, and a huge step towards creating more diversity and representation in the media raising the bar in uplifting and supporting the storytelling of more BIPOC leading stories at large. Major applause to Disney+ for providing a platform for our stories to be told.

💕 Meant the world to me to rock a culturally significant Buddhist woven bracelet on the red carpet

💎 Wearing @maisonmiru’s “Heart of Dinner System Kit” earrings that I curated with @moonlynntsai to benefit 20% of sales to @heartofdinner 😍 and @sublimajewelry Camden Curve Hoops designed by Kelly who’s been such a champion of @heartofdinner 

🎥 Thank youu @myfriendsteven for capturing a family memory! 🙏

#DisneyPlus #AmericanBornChinese

From the get-go, we wasted no time jumping into the harsh realities of building businesses and organizations, as the host of this video series @oneouncegold so aptly put it, particularly in light of the pandemic and anti-Asian violence that hit NYC hard.

My heart is still overflowing with 🥰❤️‍🩹 in conversation with some of my founder friends about our journeys @oneouncegold @nguyencoffeesupply, @kevinleeme @immieats, @alessandroroco @drinksanzo, @kimoftheinternet @omsom, @anihustles @kolkatachaico. I have the utmost respect and admiration for each of their individual stories, and it felt so nourishing to be part of this behind-the-scenes conversation.

As Asian American, Native Hawaiian, and Pacific Islander Heritage Month comes to a close, sharing a snippet from this meaningful discussion in honor of celebrating our collective work, survival, building, and dreaming together as a community.

Thank you to the wonder that is @oneouncegold of @nguyencoffeesupply who collaborated with @jxu.photo and the @wholefoods team to host a video series about what it means to support Local in New York, and how supporting NYC’s AAPI community initiatives, food and beverage, and music are all tied together. Thank you @corybng for welcoming us in with delicious Cantonese-American cuisine at @potluckclubny.

Happy Father’s Day to this incredible human who embodies kindness and compassion through his day-to-day actions and gentle words of wisdom. So grateful to have the best Dad I could ever ask for — and the best one to troll with aggressive kisses on the cheek cause I know how shy he gets 🤣❤️🥹

Wishing a very happy Father’s Day to all who father and to all those who have stepped in as a father/parent figure. Sending love to all who are touched by Father’s Day ❤️‍🩹

✨08.08✨ Grateful for all the birthday love, thank you for taking the time to think of me in your warm wishes!! Sending my love and gratitude to everyone who has uplifted and supported me throughout my life, wouldn’t be who I am without you. ❤️ 

Spending my birthday hiking through the Canadian Rockies, recharging with nature and wandering trails from my dream wish list! 🏔️🚗✨ 

Highlights include:

👉Cherries, wildflowers, gummy bears for the road 🍒🌼🐻
👉 Emerald Lake in #YohoNationalPark
👉 Car camping between stops
👉 Sunrise at Lake Louise 🌄 
👉 Tea and handmade scones, banana bread, chips & homemade hummus, tuna sandwich & soup at Lake Agnes Tea House, Canada's oldest tea house tucked away in the forest 🍵

Thank you so much to my Love @moonlynntsai for planning the most EPIC road trip ever 🙌🥰❤️

social_posts.post_text: HAPPYYYY BIRTHDAYYYY to my Love @moonlynntsai!! The stone-fruit-loving, hotpot-hosting-addict, cutest-little-way-with-her-feet, globe-trotting, culinary-genius, pun-queen!!! Thank you for lighting up this world with your damn fine sexy self (and for also bringing so much love and happiness to everyone around you with your thoughtfulness and caring heart!!) Forever wishing you JOY and endless sense of adventure!! LOVE YOU, Love of my life!!! ❤️🎉❤️🎉❤️

Dearest Soulmate, @moonlynntsai,

Here we are at 9 years, and what a wild ride it’s been. Remember that time a psychic claimed we’d been together in a past life and were destined for another round? I’d like to believe it’s true.

Grateful to you, always, for setting my soul ablaze that night we were dancing deep in the stretches of the desert. 

Countless adventures, late night heart-to-hearts, early morning giggles, and a whole lot of growing and building, here we are all these years later. And how is it I still get so excited to see you after you step out for 10 minutes to the post office (or for 3 minutes taking out the trash)?! Thank you for being my favorite person and my favorite everything. 

Nine years down, and here's to many, many more in this lifetime…and in the next. Can’t wait to dance through every version with you. ❤️

Happy anniversary, Soulmate.

Love you always,
Meep/Noodle/Mew/Meeples/MeeMaw/MeepityMoo

Overwhelmed with gratitude and inspiration at the 2023 Glamour’s Women of the Year Awards. It’s an honor to be on the advisory board recognizing and celebrating the incredible women making waves with their impact and achievements, and reuniting with the @glamourmag fam and fellow board members always feels like the holidays. ✨

A hearty congratulations to this year’s honorees @quintab, @americaferrera, @therealmaryjblige, @geenarocero, @brookeshields, @milliebobbybrown, and daring to disrupt honoree @selmablair for their work and courage. Thank you to the host of the evening and always-hilarious @michellebuteau for bringing that burst of sunshine energy all night. A massive congratulations to the incredible Glamour team who brought this magical evening to life – @sambarry, @ru_wolle, @tashpearlman, and the whole Glamour crew, you’ve outdone yourselves, raising the bar year after year— continually championing women worldwide. And a loving shoutout to @ru_wolle for producing the best after-party filled with joy!
—-
👗Honored to float through the evening in the Ellaella Pouf Dress by the extraordinarily talented Malaysian-Indonesian designer @jasminechongofficial, each red silk organza hand-pleated bloom stitched, gathered, and sewn on by hand. Wearing this masterpiece, crafted by a designer sharing my Malaysian heritage, filled me with immense pride.

💍Proudly rocking all @maisonmiru jewelry founded by the brilliant engineer and jewelry designer Trisha Okubo. Thank you so much to the incredibly talented @trishaokubo @junanw @meijia_design for styling @maisonmiru jewelry to beautifully complement the outfit.

💄All of my love to @melorayaru for the stunning makeup, aka my sister, aka the best makeup artist I’ve ever worked. Melora, thank you for truly capturing each individual’s essence like no one else.

✨Humbled and privileged to be surrounded by kindred spirits – fellow dreamers, thinkers, and creators – who lead with compassion, working tirelessly towards an inclusive world where our voices are acknowledged and valued. Grateful to everyone who made this evening possible.

Last week was a moment etched in my memory forever, joining @glamourmag at the @nyse. Standing with @sambarry, Glamour’s trailblazing EIC and fearless leader, and surrounded by her extraordinary, unstoppable team like @ru_wolle @tashpearlman @moneeeeekk, who each pour their heart and soul into everything Glamour stands for & reuniting with some fellow members of the Glamour #WOTY Advisory Board (truly some of the best reunions ever.) 

Together, we celebrated the Glamour Women of the Year awards, a tribute to the magazine’s decades-long and ongoing commitment to amplifying women’s voices worldwide. Standing there on the trading floor, in the heart of the NYC’s rapid-paced financial world, as a child of parents who courageously journeyed from Taiwan and Malaysia for a brighter future— the weight of that moment was not lost on me. 

Immediately the day after, I visited my Mom and Dad, sharing photos and videos from NYSE. They had come to America with dreams of opportunity, met and fell in love in Queens, and built a business from the ground up. They provided a life for their children that was full of opportunities, always aware of the significance of places like the NYSE as a beacon of dreams and sacrifices in their world of business. 

It was in that exact moment watching my mom’s jaw dropping in amazement, her eyes widening, and my dad, shaking his head in awe and a proud, disbelieving smile murmuring a gentle “thank you” – seeing their daughter, alongside a group of phenomenal women, ringing the bell, defying the societal norms they grew up with that often restricted women’s dreams— words fall short to fully capture the overwhelm of emotions from this occasion. 

The immeasurable investment of Glamour’s work in creating space for women’s stories and experiences was, more intimately, paralleled by my parents’ immeasurable journey filled with grit and determination to build a life of possibilities for their daughters.

A heartfelt thank you to Team Glamour and the formidable NYSE President @lynnmartin7 for this unforgettable experience.
